               <text>
                  <paragraph>AGL<br/>Auto Gas Light<br/>AIR, <br/>COMPRESSED<br/>U.N. 1002<br/>DO NOT REMOVE THIS LABEL<br/>AGL-8-D-100         1/02 MADE IN USA<br/>NON-FLAMMABLE GAS     2<br/>MEDICAL AIR, U.S.P.<br/>CAUTION: HIGH PRESSURE GAS. MAY ACCELERATE COMBUSTION.<br/>Keep oil and grease away. Use only with equipment designated for compressed air service and rated for cylinder pressure. Cylinder temperature should not exceed 52 degrees C (125 degrees F). User shall Secure cylinder in use and in storage. Use in upright position. Close valve after each use, and when empty. Keep valve protection cap in place when not in use, if so equipped. Use in accordance with MSDS sheet.<br/>WARNING: For breathing support when used by properly trained personnel. For medical applications, RX only. Administration of Medical Air may be hazardous or contraindicated. For medical use only by or under the supervision of a licensed practitioner who is experienced in the use and administration of Medical Air and is familiar with the indications, effects, dosages, methods, and frequency and duration of administration and with the hazards, contraindication and side effects and the precautions to be taken.<br/>RETURN WITH 25 PSIG.<br/>AGL Inhalation Therapy Co. Clifton, NJ 07015<br/>973-478-5100 <br/>973-478-5000<br/>Pressure:          PSIG at 70 degrees F.<br/>Size <br/>Contents      liters<renderMultiMedia referencedObject="MM1"/>
                  </paragraph>
               </text>
